HEADWORD: Unworthy
<hw>Un*wor"thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not worthy; wanting
merit, value, or fitness; undeserving; worthless; unbecoming; -- often
with <xex>of</xex>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Un*wor"thi*ly</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Un*wor"thi*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

